[{"id":42799,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>15</mn></mrow></mfrac><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ln</mi></mrow><mo>⁡</mo><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mrow></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>30</mn></mrow></mfrac><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ln</mi></mrow><mo>⁡</mo><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mrow></math>","<math><mn>2</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"Energy of a damping oscillator is&nbsp;<math><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-2</mo><mi>&#947;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math> at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp;where <math><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo></math>damping constant,&nbsp;<math><msup><mrow><mi>E</mi><mi>&#39;</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#160;</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>o</mi></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#947;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#947;</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mn>15</mn></mfenced></mrow></msup></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>30</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>&#8289;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (11 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":42760,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mi>g</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","Image is virtual, opposite side of convex mirror."],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a2782cfa-1f57-4404-a70a-3b3c4a9ab4f8-image.png\" style=\"width: 167px; height: 165px;\" /></p><p>Force along the tunnel</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mfrac></mfenced><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>r</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mi>g</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42740,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#981;</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#981;</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>Asin</mi><mi>&#981;</mi></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#981;</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>From <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#981;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#981;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>Putting the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#981;</mi></math> in equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"}\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42684,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"We know\n$\\begin{aligned}\n\\mathrm{V}_{\\max } & =\\omega \\mathrm{A} \\quad \\text { at mean position } \\\\\n& =\\frac{2 \\pi}{\\mathrm{T}} \\mathrm{A}=\\frac{2 \\pi}{\\pi} \\times 0.06=0.12 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{sec} \\\\\n\\mathrm{V}_{\\max } & =12 \\mathrm{~cm} / \\mathrm{sec}\n\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42714,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/54edda86-c83e-4104-ab1e-37ff19be5f64-f40d1b4d-f99e-4b0b-9697-66502a077b73-9894470.PNG\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 195px;\" /></p><p>The position of a particle performing an SHM is given by:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#981;</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>Since at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>, the particle is at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,&nbsp;therefore the initial phase&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#981;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p><p>At time&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>, the particle is at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#969;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Therefore, time period</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></mrow><mi>&#969;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math></p><p>The total time taken from&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>T</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>.</p><p>Since the time taken from&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>, therefore the time taken from&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (25 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42721,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/31b05ae5-a3c7-4f0a-a3a7-ac2bdd21af50-1.jpg\" style=\"width: 310px; height: 283px;\" /></p><p>In figure (a), the springs are connected in series. Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>eq</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>K</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>K</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>K</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>K</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>K</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>K</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>K</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>K</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>K</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Therefore, the time period</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>eq</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>K</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>K</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>In&nbsp;figure (b), the springs are connected in parallel. Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>K</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>K</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>K</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>K</mi></math></p><p>Therefore, the time period</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>b</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>eq</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>K</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>Now,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>b</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>b</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math></p><p>Hence,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42673,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$175$","$25 \\sqrt{7}$","$5 \\sqrt{7}$","$125$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{x}_1=\\sqrt{7} \\sin 5 \\mathrm{t} \\\\ & \\mathrm{x}_2=2 \\sqrt{7} \\sin \\left(5 \\mathrm{t}+\\frac{\\pi}{3}\\right)\\end{aligned}$<br/>From phasor,<br/><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4Kx0fElAHpb5zMDZEyiepYxWbjy8P19Z9AcOkPSLzj8.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>$\\therefore$ Amplitude of resultant $\\mathrm{SHM}=7$<br/>$\\begin{aligned} & \\phi=\\tan ^{-1} \\frac{2 \\sqrt{7} \\times \\sqrt{3} / 2}{\\sqrt{7}+2 \\sqrt{7} \\times \\frac{1}{2}}=\\tan ^{-1} \\frac{\\sqrt{21}}{2 \\sqrt{7}}=\\tan ^{-1} \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\\\ & \\therefore \\quad \\mathrm{X}_{\\mathrm{R}}=7 \\sin (5 \\mathrm{t}+\\phi) \\\\ & \\quad \\mathrm{a}_{\\mathrm{R}}=-7 \\times 25 \\sin (5 \\mathrm{t}+\\phi) \\\\ & \\therefore \\mathrm{a}_{\\max }=175 \\mathrm{~cm} / \\mathrm{sec}=175 \\times 10^{-2} \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{sec}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (2 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42784,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math><mi>A</mi></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>P</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mtd><mtd><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>K</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></math><br /><br />As given in question<br /><br /><math><mi>K</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>E</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>K</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>K</mi><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mfrac><mi>A</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42779,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$10^{-3} \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s}$","$1 \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s}$","$10^{-1} \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s}$","$10^{-5} \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"Angular frequency of pendulum $\\omega=\\sqrt{\\frac{g}{\\ell}}$\r\n\r\n$\\therefore$ relative change in angular frequency\r\n\r\n$\\frac{\\Delta \\omega}{\\omega}=\\frac{1}{2} \\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{g}}{\\mathrm{g}}[$ as length remains constant $]$\r\n\r\n$\\Delta g=2 \\mathrm{~A} \\omega_{s}^{2}\\left[\\omega_{s}=\\right.$ angular frequency of support and, $\\mathrm{A}=$\r\n\r\namplitude]\r\n\r\n$\\frac{\\Delta \\omega}{\\omega}=\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{2 \\mathrm{~A} \\omega_{\\mathrm{S}}^{2}}{\\mathrm{~g}}$\r\n\r\n$\\Delta \\omega=\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{2 \\times 1^{2} \\times 10^{-2}}{10}=10^{-3} \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{sec}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42829,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["at the highest position of the platform","at the mean position of the platform","for an amplitude of $\\frac{\\mathrm{g}}{\\omega^2}$","for an amplitude of $\\frac{\\mathrm{g}^2}{\\omega^2}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$A \\omega^2=g$\n$\\Rightarrow A=g / \\omega^2$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2006","image":null},{"id":42711,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given here, displacement&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Now, potential energy of a simple harmonic oscillator is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>,</p><p>So, slope of potential energy and time curve is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>U</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></math></p><p>Now,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>U</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub></math>&nbsp;will be maximum when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mi>T</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>T</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42780,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$\\frac{1}{9}$","1","2","$\\frac{1}{3}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"Kinetic energy, $\\mathrm{k}=\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{~m} \\omega^{2} \\mathrm{~A}^{2} \\cos ^{2} \\omega \\mathrm{t}$\r\n\r\nPotential energy, $U=\\frac{1}{2} m \\omega^{2} A^{2} \\sin ^{2} \\omega t$\r\n\r\n$\\frac{k}{U}=\\cot ^{2} \\omega t=\\cot ^{2} \\frac{\\pi}{90}(210)=\\frac{1}{3}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42745,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/253f118a-9e2f-4b61-8bf6-2990aa0e25a0-image.png\" style=\"width: 301px; height: 225px;\" /></p><p>Applying work energy theorem:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>w</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>w</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>K</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>l</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>l</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42761,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mi>k</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mi>k</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>For parallel combination&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>k</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>k</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>k</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><msub><mi>k</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mi>k</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42667,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["7.5","0.75","120","15"],"answer":0,"solution":"Period of simple pendulum: $T = \\frac{\\text{time}}{\\text{number of oscillations}}$<br>Initial period: $T_1 = \\frac{10}{20} = 0.5$ s<br>Required period: $T_2 = \\frac{10}{40} = 0.25$ s<br>Using $T = 2\\pi\\sqrt{\\frac{L}{g}}$, the ratio is: $\\frac{T_2}{T_1} = \\sqrt{\\frac{L_2}{L_1}}$<br>$\\frac{0.25}{0.5} = \\sqrt{\\frac{L_2}{30}} \\Rightarrow 0.5 = \\sqrt{\\frac{L_2}{30}}$<br>$0.25 = \\frac{L_2}{30} \\Rightarrow L_2 = 7.5$ cm","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42659,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$2\\pi\\sqrt{\\dfrac{5R}{4g}}$","$2\\pi\\sqrt{\\dfrac{2R}{3g}}$","$2\\pi\\sqrt{\\dfrac{3R}{2g}}$","$2\\pi\\sqrt{\\dfrac{3R}{g}}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"From the given figure, the axis of rotation is a horizontal line passing through the point $A$ on the edge of the disc. The circular arrow around the axis indicates that the disc oscillates out of its plane, meaning the axis of rotation is a tangent to the disc in its own plane.<br><br>The moment of inertia of a uniform disc about its diameter is $I_{cm} = \\dfrac{1}{4}MR^2$.<br><br>Using the parallel axis theorem, the moment of inertia of the disc about the given axis of rotation is:<br>$I = I_{cm} + MR^2 = \\dfrac{1}{4}MR^2 + MR^2 = \\dfrac{5}{4}MR^2$<br><br>The distance from the center of mass of the disc to the axis of rotation is $d = R$.<br><br>The time period of a physical pendulum is given by:<br>$T = 2\\pi\\sqrt{\\dfrac{I}{Mgd}}$<br><br>Substituting the values of $I$ and $d$:<br>$T = 2\\pi\\sqrt{\\dfrac{\\dfrac{5}{4}MR^2}{MgR}} = 2\\pi\\sqrt{\\dfrac{5R}{4g}}$<br><br>Answer: $2\\pi\\sqrt{\\dfrac{5R}{4g}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (04 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42742,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>&#960;&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>g</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/df9876de-3200-4207-a547-e0bb77b1f82d-image.png\" style=\"width: 367px; height: 164px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br />as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>&#8776;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>&#8776;</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">K</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">q</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">x</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42741,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>K</mi><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>E</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>K</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mi>v</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>K</mi><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>K</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42833,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["first increase and then decrease to the original value.","first decreased then increase to the original value.","remain unchanged.","increase towards a saturation value."],"answer":0,"solution":"First CM goes down and then comes to its initial position","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":42710,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>50</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p><p>Comparing with standard equation of SHM,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><msqrt><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Now,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mi>&#969;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>88</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Hence, required <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>88</mn></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42835,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{T}=\\mathrm{t}_1+\\mathrm{t}_2$","$\\propto \\mathrm{x}^2$","$\\mathrm{T}^{-1}=\\mathrm{t}_1^{-1}+\\mathrm{t}_2^{-1}$","$\\mathrm{T}^{-2}=\\mathrm{t}_1^2+\\mathrm{t}_2^2$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$t_1^2+t_2^2=T^2$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":42656,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$\\dfrac{5\\sqrt{50}}{\\pi}$ and $8 \\times 10^{-3}$","$\\dfrac{5\\sqrt{50}}{\\pi}$ and $8$","$10\\sqrt{50}$ and $2 \\times 10^{-3}$","$\\dfrac{5\\sqrt{50}}{\\pi}$ and $16 \\times 10^{-3}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"At equilibrium, the restoring force of the spring balances the weight of the mass:<br><br>$mg = kx_0$<br><br>$k = \\dfrac{mg}{x_0} = \\dfrac{0.2 \\times 10}{2 \\times 10^{-3}} = 1000$ N/m<br><br>The frequency of oscillation is given by:<br><br>$f = \\dfrac{1}{2\\pi} \\sqrt{\\dfrac{k}{m}}$<br><br>$f = \\dfrac{1}{2\\pi} \\sqrt{\\dfrac{1000}{0.2}} = \\dfrac{1}{2\\pi} \\sqrt{5000} = \\dfrac{10\\sqrt{50}}{2\\pi} = \\dfrac{5\\sqrt{50}}{\\pi}$ Hz<br><br>The maximum energy in the spring corresponds to its maximum elastic potential energy, which occurs at the maximum extension.<br><br>Maximum extension $x_{max} = x_0 + A = 2 \\text{ mm} + 2 \\text{ mm} = 4 \\text{ mm} = 4 \\times 10^{-3}$ m<br><br>Maximum energy in the spring $U_{max} = \\dfrac{1}{2} k x_{max}^2$<br><br>$U_{max} = \\dfrac{1}{2} \\times 1000 \\times (4 \\times 10^{-3})^2$<br><br>$U_{max} = 500 \\times 16 \\times 10^{-6} = 8000 \\times 10^{-6} = 8 \\times 10^{-3}$ J<br><br>Answer: $\\dfrac{5\\sqrt{50}}{\\pi}$ and $8 \\times 10^{-3}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (06 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42697,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The formula to calculate the kinetic energy&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>K</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;of a particle executing SHM is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">=</mo><mfrac><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>k</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Substitute the values of the known parameters into equation (1) and solve to calculate the value of the unknown parameter.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>K</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfenced></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>200</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi></msup></mrow><mn>100</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (13 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42765,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#945;</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#945;</mi></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/458d011e-1844-444b-a815-bd7c917871fd-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 180px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>eq</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>K</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>K</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>K</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>K</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>eq</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (24 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42732,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>From the figure, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mfenced><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mi>&#969;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>&#8467;</mi><msub><mi>g</mi><mi>p</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>g</mi><mi>p</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>g</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>/</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (01 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42698,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The formula to calculate the potential energy of the particle executing SHM is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>The formula to calculate the kinetic energy of the same particle is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Divide equation (1) by equation (2) to obtain the required ratio.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mi>P</mi><mi>K</mi></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Substitute&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;into equation (3) to calculate the required ratio.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mi>P</mi><mi>K</mi></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msup><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mstyle><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42671,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$\\theta_1 l_2^2=\\theta_2 l_1^2$","$\\theta_1 l_1=\\theta_2 l_2$","$\\theta_1 l_1^2=\\theta_2 l_2^2$","$\\theta_1 l_2=\\theta_2 l_1$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\omega=\\sqrt{\\frac{\\mathrm{g}}{\\ell}} \\\\ & \\alpha=-\\omega^2 \\theta \\\\ & \\therefore \\frac{\\mathrm{~g}}{\\ell_1} \\theta_1=\\frac{\\mathrm{g}}{\\ell_2} \\theta_2 \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\theta_1 \\ell_2=\\theta_2 \\ell_2\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (4 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42832,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$\\frac{2 \\pi}{\\alpha}$","$\\frac{2 \\pi}{\\sqrt{\\alpha}}$","$2 \\pi \\alpha$","$2 \\pi \\sqrt{\\alpha}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\omega^2=\\alpha$\n$\\omega=\\sqrt{\\alpha}$\n$T=\\frac{2 \\pi}{\\sqrt{\\alpha}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":42663,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["5","27","20","30"],"answer":3,"solution":"Two masses (1 kg and 0.2 kg) connected by a spring (k = 150 N/m) on a frictionless surface undergo oscillation about their center of mass.<br>This two-body problem reduces to SHM with reduced mass $\\mu = \\frac{m_1 m_2}{m_1 + m_2} = \\frac{1 \\times 0.2}{1.2} = \\frac{1}{6}$ kg.<br>The angular frequency is $\\omega = \\sqrt{\\frac{k}{\\mu}} = \\sqrt{\\frac{150}{1/6}} = \\sqrt{900} = 30$ rad/s.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (28 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42736,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>[</mo><mi>sin</mi><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>]</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Aug Shift 2)","image":null}]